<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idefbf963e-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s4804"><num value="4804">§ 4804.</num><heading> Notice and hearing</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">During the period beginning on <date date="1986-01-01">January 1, 1986</date>, and ending 30 days after receipt of a proposal for an initial order submitted by any person affected by this chapter, the Secretary shall—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idefbf963f-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s4804/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> publish such proposed order; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idefbf9640-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s4804/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> give due notice of and opportunity for public comment on such proposed order.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idefbf9641-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/99/198/tXVI/s1615">Pub. L. 99–198, title XVI, § 1615</ref>, <date date="1985-12-23">Dec. 23, 1985</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/99/1609">99 Stat. 1609</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idefbf9642-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idefbf9643-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idefbf9644-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1986-01-01">Jan. 1, 1986</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/99/198/s1631">section 1631 of Pub. L. 99–198</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s4801">section 4801 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
